item.content:encoded:
Live "la dolce vita"! Enjoy a video visit to Capri, and the Amalfi Coast before exploring the stunning region of Puglia. Then, end in Rome... the fabulous eternal city.

&nbsp;

Let's <strong><a href="/contact/">start planning</a></strong> and booking your next great adventure.

An epic journey to a land full of wonders. Egypt, is a destination that's pretty much on everyone's bucket list, and there's no better time to experience than now. Visit the archeological sites without the huge crowds, marvel at King Tut's treasures practically on your own and enjoy great saving on the experience while you can.

&nbsp;

Take a peak at our recent adventure, and see why we're already dreaming of our return. Endless riches, kind and welcoming people, fabulous accommodations, delicious food and the most generous tour operators anywhere. Let's begin planning your own epic journey to the land of the Pharaohs today!

Eden For Your World had the pleasure of attending Travel Week Sao Paolo for the third year in a row.  The 2014 edition was fantastic, like previous years.  However, this was the inaugural year of the show's merger with International Luxury Travel Market (ILTM).

Between May 6-9th luxury travel agents and suppliers descend upon the vibrant city of Sao Paolo and unite under the roof of the Bienal Pavillion, designed by renowned architect Oscar Niemeyer, at Ibirapuera Park.  Meetings and collaborations are on the agenda from 9am-6pm.  Afterwards, dinners and cocktails become a more relaxed atmosphere for all of us to gather and talk business and fun!

During shows like this, we are afforded the greatest luxuries available on earth... connections with suppliers on site and in locations where our clients will be heading.  These connections are why we choose to travel far distances.  Our participation and our personal experiences work to make our clients future travel's true 'eden' experiences!

Enjoy a brief 30 second recap of Travel Week Sao Paolo:  <a href="http://www.edenforyourworld.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/TWSP14.mov">TWSP14</a>

&nbsp;

&nbsp;

&nbsp;

&nbsp;

&nbsp;

